				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I could be wrong, but our pets have mana pools too...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Assuming they do have mana pools, what is the use, and what is the benefit?  Since our pets proc on attacks, not cast spells, there is no use for mana pools; and that is even without going into the fact that I have never seen my pet not be able to proc (thus assuming that it had somehow run out of mana) except in situations where resists or level are a factor.  
<br />

<br />
Also, you mention visable differences to stats using buffs.  There have been at times extensive parsings (many done by Coprolith, here and at beastlords.org -- let me see if I can locate them) that have shown that neither STA nor AGI make any difference when it comes to warders.  HP buffs like Kragg and Virtue make a difference to a pet, but they gain no additional hp benefits from IOS/Focus/STA.
<br />

<br />
If you have any evidence to the contrary (and I will attempt to provide evidence to prove my view) then feel free to post, I would definitely be interested in seeing it.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=545758" target=new><img src="http://www.campleadership.com/images/mtinie.jpg"></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
